          "description": "Infrastructural awareness remained minimal in mainstream culture, though the collapse of Soviet infrastructure systems following the USSR's dissolution provided some glimpses into the fragility of large-scale systems. Academic interest in large technological systems was growing, particularly in science and technology studies. The internet was expanding but still primarily conceived in terms of information rather than physical infrastructure. Some early digital artists began exploring network aesthetics, though their audience remained limited.",
