          "variance_explained": 0.01,
          "description": "In 1989, ambient awareness existed primarily as a theoretical concept explored by early digital theorists and researchers in computer-mediated communication. The concept was largely limited to academic discussions of how emerging computer networks might create new forms of social awareness. With limited internet access and no social media platforms, the general public had virtually no experience with digital ambient awareness, though early BBS (Bulletin Board Systems) users began experiencing primitive forms of persistent social connection.",
