      "description": "Sensory Recalibration refers to the ongoing cultural process of adjusting human perceptual systems to rapidly changing technological, environmental, and social conditions. This eigencluster tracks how individuals and communities develop new sensory frameworks to navigate an increasingly mediated reality, where digital interfaces, environmental shifts, and technological extensions of the body require constant perceptual adaptation. The cluster encompasses theoretical frameworks from embodied cognition, phenomenology, and media studies that examine how our sensory apparatus is being rewired through technological engagement. It also includes artistic practices that deliberately manipulate sensory experience to highlight or critique these changes, medical and psychological research on sensory processing disorders and adaptations, and emerging design philosophies that account for multisensory experience in increasingly virtual or hybrid environments. As digital technologies have become more immersive and ubiquitous, this cluster has gained significance, reflecting growing cultural awareness of how our fundamental modes of perception are being transformed.",
